  "lesson": {
    "title": "Pushbutton RC Delay",
    "description": "Press and hold the tact button. A 4.7kΩ resistor and 1000µF capacitor (τ ≈ 4.7 s) slow the rise — the red LED on the east branch is in parallel with the cap, so it brightens gradually instead of snapping on like lesson 8. Release the button and the LED fades out as the cap discharges. Cap on the center column; LED east at 90° (anode north)."
